  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). A binding Requirement mandates experimental-validation as the required verification method; however, the supporting ValidationResult was generated by a numerical-simulation activity. The narrative presents the high-fidelity simulation as functionally equivalent to bench testing, but the structured activityType disagrees with the requiredVerificationMethod, instantiating weakener W-AR-03.",
